    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-02T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-02T03:00:00-05:00" n="675"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d675">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1039/10930: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-02T09:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 2, 1944—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9:02 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3507. The following telegram has been sent to London.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>911, June 2, 9 a.m. Nil quota for piston rings included in counter proposals
                        forwarded Swiss on May 25 (Embassy’s 147, May 30<note n="46"
                            xml:id="d675fn1">See telegram 4334, May 30, 9 p.m., from London, <ref
                                target="#pg_724">p. 724</ref>.</note> and Department’s 1818, May 26
                        to Bern, repeated to London). CA<note n="47" xml:id="d675fn2">Commercial
                            Attaché (American).</note> and CS<note n="48" xml:id="d675fn3"
                            >Commercial Secretary (British).</note> do not see any advantage in
                        treating piston rings separately from other items covered by negotiations
                        and believe it advisable in any case to await Swiss reply to May 25 letters.
                        Swiss have been requested supply statistics exports piston rings to Germany
                        and other Axis [countries] since first of year.</p>
                    <p>Repeated to Department as my 3507.</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
